The Problem
We have a bunch of events that come from different parts of our application(new user signs up, new user does something for the first time, etc.). Each event then triggers some action, some of which are themselves events(much like recursive function).  
So, how do we implement someftware when we're faced with such a complex system? But, what do I mean by a "complex system"? This is what I mean:  
1. Events should be handled asynchronously. For example, we don't want to make the user wait while we send an email.  
2. Some events are dealt with immediately. Some events trigger actions in the future, like an scheduled event.
3. Consequences of events should be configurable, configurable by non-developers. The manager wants to change things up pretty quickly, so even if he can't do it, I should be able to do it within a day!!   
4. We want to code clean code. That means automated tests and readable code that just works.

